175 Good, Clean Jokes That’ll Make You Laugh Your Pants Off

Share these funny jokes with friends and family members.

Jan 2, 2026 12:18 PM EST
By Maryn Liles
Lifestyle Writer, Parade

Funny clean jokes make every conversation better—whether you’re sharing a laugh with a friend or entertaining your kids—and these G-rated jokes are no exception.

From the best clean jokes for adults to clean jokes of the day, this big list has something for everyone, so you can feel good about busting out these hilarious SFW funnies, no matter who it is you’re talking to—from your grandma to your coworker.

Read on to discover the best clean jokes that promise a whole lot of giggles for both adults and kids alike.

Related: 80 New Year’s Jokes to Crack You Up Long After the Ball Drops at Midnight

Table of Contents

  1. Clean Jokes That'll Make You Laugh
  2. The Best Clean Jokes for Kids
  3. Corny Clean Jokes
  4. Clean Jokes for a Hilarious Joke of the Day
  5. Clean Jokes for Adults

Clean Jokes That’ll Make You Laugh

1. Did you hear about the first restaurant to open on the moon?
It had great food, but no atmosphere.

2. Why don’t scientists trust atoms?
Because they make up everything!

3. What do dentists call their X-rays?
Tooth pics!

4. What did one ocean say to the other ocean?
Nothing, it just waved.

5. What did the big flower say to the little flower?
“Hi, bud!”

6. Did you hear about the fire at the circus?
It was in tents!

7. Why do ducks have feathers?
To cover their butt quacks!

8. What’s the difference between a hippo and a zippo?
One is really heavy, and the other’s a little lighter.

9. What does a nosey pepper do?
It gets jalapeño business.

10. Why should you never trust stairs?
They’re always up to something.

🎬 SIGN UP for Parade’s Daily newsletter to get the latest pop culture news & celebrity interviews delivered right to your inbox. 🎬

11. When does a joke become a “dad” joke?
When it becomes apparent.

12. Why did the bullet end up losing his job?
He got fired.

13. What kind of shorts do clouds wear?
Thunderpants.

14. I entered ten puns in a contest to see which would win.
No pun in ten did.

15. How do you measure a snake?
In inches—they don’t have feet.

16. Where does a waitress with only one leg work?
IHOP.

17. What does a house wear?
Address!

18. Why are toilets always so good at poker?
They always get a flush.

19. Why is Peter Pan always flying?
Because he Neverlands. (I love this joke because it never grows old.)

20. You heard the rumor going around about butter?
Never mind, I shouldn’t spread it.

Related: 165 Knock-Knock Jokes for Kids and Adults That Are So Bad They’re Funny Good

21. Two windmills are standing on a wind farm. One asks, “What’s your favorite kind of music?” The other replies, “I’m a big metal fan.”

22. What did one DNA say to the other?
“Do these genes make me look fat?”

23. How do you make an egg roll?
You push it.

24. What has more lives than a cat?
A frog. It croaks every day!

25. Why does Norway put barcodes on its battleships?
To Scandinavian.

26. What did one plate say to the other?
Dinner’s on me.

27. Why do cows have hooves instead of feet?
Because they lactose.

28. What’s a skeleton’s least favorite room?
The living room.

29. If at first, you don’t succeed …
Skydiving is not for you.

The Best Clean Jokes for Kids

30. How does NASA organize a party?
They planet.

31. The first rule of the Alzheimer’s club is…
Wait, where are we again?

32. I took the shell off of my racing snail, thinking it would make him faster. But if anything, it made him more sluggish.

33. What do you get from a pampered cow?
Spoiled milk.

34. What’s the best thing about Switzerland?
I don’t know, but the flag is a big plus.

35. Why did the bicycle fall over?
Because it was two-tired!

36. How many tickles does it take to get an octopus to laugh?
Ten tickles.

37. Why doesn’t Dracula have any friends?
Well, honestly, he’s a real pain in the neck.

38. My teachers told me I’d never amount to much since I procrastinate a lot.
I told them, “Just you wait!”

39. Why were they called the “dark ages?”
Because there were a lot of knights.

40. What gets wetter the more it dries?
A towel.

41. Why aren’t koalas considered bears?
They don’t have the right koala-fications.

42. You: What cartoon mouse walks on two feet?
Them: Mickey Mouse

43. You: What duck walks on two feet?
Them: Donald Duck
You: No, all ducks do!

44. Want to hear a joke about a roof?
The first one’s on the house.

45. What’s a pirate’s favorite letter?
You probably think it’s “R” but it be the “C.”

Related: 75 ‘Old People Jokes’ for Seniors to Laugh at and Feel Seen

46. How come teddy bears never want to eat anything?
Because they’re always stuffed.

47. Did you hear about the cheese factory that exploded in France?
There was nothing left but de Brie.

48. Where should you go in the room if you’re feeling cold?
The corner—they’re usually 90 degrees.

49. I can never take my dog to the park because the ducks keep trying to bite him.
I guess that’s what I get for buying a pure bread dog.

50. What’s the difference between a poorly dressed man on a unicycle and a well-dressed man on a bicycle?
Attire.

51. What did the Buddhist ask the hot dog vendor?
“Make me one with everything.”

52. You know why you never see elephants hiding up in trees?
Because they’re really good at it.

53. What happens to an illegally parked frog?
It gets toad away.

54. What’s a dog’s favorite homework assignment?
A lab report.

55. Why did the rooster cross the road?
To prove he wasn’t a chicken.

56. Why don’t cats play poker in the jungle?
Too many cheetahs.

57. How did the barber win the race?
He knew a shortcut.

58. How does a rancher keep track of his cattle?
With a cow-culator.

59. When does a duck wake up?
At the quack of dawn.

60. What do sea monsters eat?
Fish and ships.

Corny Clean Jokes

61. How did the hipster burn his mouth?
He ate his pizza before it was cool.

62. A horse walks into a bar.
The bartender says, “Why the long face?”

63. What do you get when you cross a dyslexic, an insomniac and an agnostic?
Someone who lays awake at night wondering if there’s a dog.

64. As a scarecrow, people say I’m outstanding in my field.
But hay, it’s in my jeans.

65. Why don’t blind people skydive?
Because it scares their dogs.

66. What’s the difference between an oral thermometer and a rectal thermometer?
The taste, mostly.

67. I stayed up all night and tried to figure out where the Sun was.
Then, it dawned on me.

68. I told my friend ten jokes to make him laugh.
Sadly, no pun in ten did.

69. I couldn’t believe the highway department called my dad a thief.
But when I got home, the signs were all there.

70. Why did the cowboy get a wiener dog?
He wanted to get a long little doggie.

71. Can a kangaroo jump higher than the Empire State Building?
Of course! The Empire State Building can’t jump.

Related: 200 Truly Corny Jokes

72. What did the duck say when it bought some lipstick?
“Put it on my bill.”

73. George Clooney, Leonardo DiCaprio and Matthew McConaughey get together to make a movie. Clooney says, “I’ll direct.” DiCaprio says, “I’ll act.” McConaughey says, “I’ll write, I’ll write, I’ll write.”

74. A horse walks into a bar.
The bartender says, “Hey!”
The horse replies, “Sure.”

75. I googled “Rorshach test.” But for some reason, all that came up were pictures of my parents fighting.

76. What do we want?
Low-flying airplane noises!
When do we want them?
Nnnnneeeeeeeeeeoooooooooow!

77. I tried to win a suntanning competition.
But all I got was bronze.

78. What do you call fake spaghetti?
An impasta!

79. Why don’t seagulls fly over the bay?
Because then they’d be bagels.

80. What do you call malware on a Kindle?
A bookworm.

81. Did you hear about the painter who was hospitalized?
The doctors say it was due to too many strokes.

82. What did the tie say to the hat?You go on ahead. I’ll hang around.

Related: These 125 Funny Puns Will Have You Giggling All Day

83. How does the man in the moon get his hair cut?
Eclipse it.

84. Did you hear about the claustrophobic astronaut?
He just wanted a little more space.

85. Why can’t your nose be 12 inches long?
Because then it would be a foot.

86. How do you impress a female baker?
Bring her flours.

87. Why did the baby strawberry cry?
Because his parents were in a jam.

88. How do you fix a cracked pumpkin?
With a pumpkin patch.

89. What did one wall say to the other?
“I’ll meet you at the corner.”

90. How do you identify a dogwood tree?
By its bark.

Clean Jokes for a Hilarious Joke of the Day

91. Why are crabs so bad at sharing?
Because they’re all shellfish.

92. How do you make a tissue dance?
Put a little boogie in it.

93. What do you call a cow with a twitch?
Beef jerky.

94. I started a new job as a tailor last week.
It’s been sew-sew.

95. What concert only costs 45 cents?
50 Cent featuring Nickleback.

96. What kind of shoes does a spy wear?
Sneakers.

97. I’ve been trying to make a sarcastic club, but it’s been really hard to tell if people are interested in joining or not.

98. And the Lord said unto John, “Come forth, and you will receive eternal life.”
But John came fifth and won a toaster.

99. Why don’t some fish play piano?
Because you can’t tuna fish!

100. My wife accused me the other day of being too immature.
I told her there were no girls allowed in my fort.

101. Someone stole my mood ring yesterday.
I still don’t know how I feel about that.

102. A Roman legionnaire walks into a bar, holds up two fingers and says, “Five beers, please.”

103. I tried to catch fog yesterday.
Mist.

104. Working in a mirror factory is something I can totally see myself doing.

105. Someone stole my Microsoft Office, and they’re gonna pay.
You have my Word.

106. What do you call a dog with no legs?
It doesn’t matter, it’s not going to come anyway.

Related: 300 Funny Dad Jokes

107. You know what they say about cliffhangers…

108. Why does a chicken coop only have two doors?
Because if it had four doors, it would be a chicken sedan.

109. A sandwich walks into a bar.
The bartender says, “Sorry, we don’t serve food here.”

110. Why are frogs always so happy?They eat whatever bugs them.

111. The sky was looking ominous so I asked Siri, “Surely, it’s not going to rain today?” And she replied, “Yes it is, and don’t call me Shirley.” That was when I realized I’d left my phone on Airplane mode.

112. Why did the giraffe get such bad grades?
He always had his head stuck in the clouds.

113. My IQ test results came back.
They were negative.

114. I was addicted to the hokey pokey.
But then I turned myself around.

115. I ordered a chicken and an egg online.
I’ll let you know which one comes first.

116. Time flies like an arrow.
Fruit flies like a banana.

117. Did you hear about the guy who invented Altoids?
They say he made a mint.

118. I was writing a book about glue.
I got stuck on the first chapter.

119. Stop looking for the perfect match.
Use a lighter.

120. Two vegetarians get in an argument …
Is it still called a beef?

Clean Jokes for Adults

121. I got a new job last week as the new top dog at Old MacDonald’s farm.
I’m the new C-I-E-I-O.

122. Whenever you jump on a trampoline, did you know it changes the season?
No matter what time of year, it always becomes spring time.

123. Why didn’t the skeleton go to the dance?
Because he had no body to go with.

124. What do you call a musician with problems?
A trebled man.

125. Where do snowmen keep their savings?
In the snowbank.

126. What do you call a religious person who sleepwalks?
A roamin’ Catholic.

127. Did you hear about the carrot detective?
He always got to the root of every case.

128. What washes up on very small beaches?
Micro-waves.

129. What did one elevator say to the other?
I think I’m coming down with something.

130. What happened when a faucet, a tomato and some lettuce ran a race together?
The lettuce was ahead, the faucet was running and the tomato was trying to ketchup.

131. What do you call a belt with a watch on it?
A waist of time.

132. Why did the tomato turn red?
It saw the salad dressing.

133. What did the grape do when it got stepped on?
It let out a little wine.

134. Why won’t skeletons fight each other?
They just don’t have the guts.

135. What do you call cheese that isn’t yours?
Nacho cheese!

136. What do you call a cow with no legs?
Ground beef.

Related: 180 Funny Quotes That Will Make You LOL!

137. What do you call a bear with no teeth?
A gummy bear.

138. What do you call a lazy kangaroo?
A pouch potato.

139. What do you call an alligator in a vest?
An in-vest-igator.

140. How did the cucumber become a pickle?
It went through a jarring experience.

141. What’s brown and really sticky?
A stick.

142. What do you call a sleeping bull?
A bulldozer.

143. How many paranoid people does it take to change a light bulb?
Who wants to know?!

144. What do you call a guy who’s had too much to drink?
A cab.

145. What do you call a sad cup of coffee?
A depresso.

146. What happens if you don’t pay your exorcist?
You get repossessed.

147. I saw a sign that said, “Watch for children.”
I thought, “That sounds like a fair trade”.

148. Why is it that if you donate a kidney, people love you …
But if you donate five kidneys, they call the police?

149. What is the best way to criticize your boss?
Very quietly.

150. Why did the ghost go to rehab?
He was addicted to boos.

Short Clean Jokes

151. Do you want to hear a construction joke?
Sorry, I’m still working on it.

152. What’s green and can sing?
Elvis Parsley.

153. Why was the belt arrested?
It was caught holding up a pair of pants.

154. What the the thesaurus eat for breakfast?
A synonym roll.

155. Why did the frog take the bus to work?
His car got toad.

156. What do you call a pig that knows karate?
A pork chop.

157. What do you call a horse that lives next door?
A neigh-bor.

158. Why do fish live in salt water?
Because pepper makes them sneeze.

159. What did the Dalmatian say after lunch?
That hit the spot!

160. What did the left eye say to the right eye?
Between us, something smells!

161. Why can’t you hear a pterodactyl when they go to the bathroom?
Because their “P” is silent!

162. What do you call a dinosaur with an extensive vocabulary?
A thesaurus. 

163. What do you get when you cross a bear and a skunk?
Winnie the Pew.

164. What do you call a snowman in the summer?
A puddle.

165. Why did the banana go to the hospital?
It wasn’t peeling well.

166. Why do cows like to stay up late? 
They like to read the moos-paper.

167. Why do bees have sticky hair?
Because they use honeycombs.

168. Why was Cinderella so bad at soccer? 
She kept running away from the ball.

169. What do you call two birds that are in love?
Tweethearts.

170. What do you call a dog magician?
A labracadabrador.

171. What do you call a fish with no eyes?
Fsh.

172. How do scientists freshen their breath?
With experi-mints.

173. What do you get when you cross a snowman and a vampire?
Frostbite.

174. Why did the math book look so sad?
It had a lot of problems.

175. Why did the golfer bring two pairs of pants? 
In case he got a hole-in-one.
